Abom Konkomba is a small and remote village in the Kintampo South District of the Brong-Ahafo Region in Ghana, where farming is vital for the communities. The village had no access road. But Abom Konkomba now benefits from the "Northern Rural Growth programme" (NRGP), a collaboration between the African Development Bank (AfDB) and the International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD). Read more. More about AfDB in this BRIEFING.&nbsp;